<div><h3>TA 214 - Shakespeare in Action </h3>  <hr>This acting course concentrates on the major works (Hamlet, Macbeth, Twelfth Night, Romeo and Juliet, etc.), giving the actor an introduction to Shakespeare. The actor is encouraged to maintain the same approach and techniques used in other scene work, while adding the challenge of verse and heightened language. The focus of the class is to take a Shakespearean play and create the illusion of the first-time performance.<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Offered periodically<br><br></div>		</td>
